Key Match Events: Netherlands won the match by 5 wickets to move to the top of the table in Group A
Bas de Leede scored an unbeaten 30 to guide the Dutch home
Vikramjit Singh scored 39 off 31 balls for Netherlands
Jan Frylink bowled a wicket-maiden on the 17th over for Namibia
Namibia were restricted to 121 for 6 in 20 overs
Pre-Game Insights: Namibia captain Gerhard Erasmus said they were looking to continue their winning run
Netherlands batter Bas de Leede said they had self-belief and were looking forward to facing Sri Lanka next
Post-Match Reflections: Netherlands captain Scott Edwards said they were focused on winning the third game in a row
Bas de Leede said it was nice to get two tight games go their way
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played between Namibia and the Netherlands in Geelong
The Dutch defeated UAE in their first match and Namibia stunned Asia Cup 2022 champions Sri Lanka in their opening game
